cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the design and performance of communication protocols for vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs), which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of shadow fading on the received signal power in V2V communication, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - VANETs can be considered as a type of multiagent system, where vehicles act as agents communicating with each other. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a shadow fading model to be incorporated into existing VANET simulators, which involves system-level simulations and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses video information recorded during the measurements to separate the measurement data into different categories, which can be considered as a multimedia application.
